** Among other nominees two other Marvel projects were nominated for this Award as well, ''[[WandaVision]]'' and ''[[Loki (TV series)|Loki]]'' (Season 1). ''WandaVision'' won the Award.

| Notes                   = * [[Xu Wenwu (Earth-199999)|The Mandarin]]'s existence in the MCU was first referenced in the {{sl|Marvel One-Shot: All Hail the King}}, following the appearance of a [[Trevor Slattery (Earth-199999)|fabricated version]] in the film {{sl|Iron Man 3 (film)}}.
**There is a little discrepancy upon the Name "The Mandarin" During the One-shot the Interviewer tells Trevor that the 10 rings organization has a story very tight to the man known as The Mandarin, character which he (Trevor) appropriated. However during this film, even though Xu Wenwu does states that he has been known through the years by many names, he also says that "The Mandarin" is a funny name the [[Advanced Idea Mechanics (Earth-199999)|Americans]] created to put a face to the 10 rings organization, so it is unclear if he truly had been known as The Mandarin in the past.
** The name Wenwu comes from a {{WP|Wen and wu|concept of Chinese administration and philosophy}}, wen means civilian and wu means military or martial, {{WP|Mandarin (bureaucrat)|Mandarin}}, is a term created by the Portuguese to describe a bureaucratic position in China, Korea and Vietnam.
* The film has had multiple release date changes due to the {{WP|COVID-19 pandemic|COVID-19 pandemic}}:
** Originally announced to release on February 12, 2021, the film was pushed back on April 3, 2020, along with Marvel's entire Phase Four line-up, to the new release date of May 7, 2021.{{cite|ref=true|url= https://variety.com/2020/film/box-office/disney-mulan-black-widow-release-dates-coronavirus-1203550173/|title= ‘Black Widow,’ ‘Eternals,’ ‘Indiana Jones 5’ and More Disney Films Get New Release Dates|work= Variety|last= Rubin|first= Rebecca|date= April 3, 2020|accessdate= April 3, 2020}}
** In September 2020, the film was pushed back again to July 9, 2021.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/black-widow-west-side-story-eternals-release-date-delay-1234773491/|title=‘Black Widow,’ ‘West Side Story,’ ‘Eternals’ Postpone Release Dates|accessdate=24 September 2020|last=Lang|first=Brent|coauthors=Rubin, Rebecca|date=23 September 2020|work=Variety}} 
** In March 2021, the film was pushed back a final time to September 3, 2021.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.marvel.com/articles/movies/black-widow-release-date-disney-plus|title=‘Black Widow’ Jumps Into New July Release Date in Theaters and on Disney+ with Premier Access|last=Paige|first=Rachel|work=Marvel|date=23 March 2021|accessdate=21 April 2021}}
* Filming for this film started in February 2020,{{cite|ref=true|url= https://deadline.com/2020/03/shang-chi-director-destin-daniel-cretton-tests-negative-for-coronavirus-says-social-distancing-is-an-act-of-love-for-every-person-1202885191/|title= ‘Shang-Chi’ Director Destin Daniel Cretton Tests Negative For Coronavirus, Says “Social Distancing Is An Act Of Love…For Every Person”|work= Deadline|last= D'Alessandro|first= Anthony|date= March 16, 2020|accessdate= October 24, 2020}} and wrapped on October 24, 2020.{{cite|ref=true|url= https://www.instagram.com/p/CGt_BaoJ76Z/|title= WE. ARE. WRAPPED!|work= Instagram|last= Cretton|first= Destin Daniel|date= October 24, 2020|accessdate= October 24, 2020}}
| Trivia                  = * Jiang Nan actress {{WP|Michelle Yeoh}} had previously portrayed the [[Earth-199999|MCU]] character [[Aleta Ogord (Earth-199999)|Aleta Ogord]] in the film {{ml|Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2 (film)}}.
** Marvel Studios President [[Kevin Feige]] asked ''Guardians of the Galaxy'' writer and director [[James Gunn]] beforehand if he would care about Yeoh's recast, to which Gunn stated he wouldn't.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://twitter.com/JamesGunn/status/1357495607724806147|title=I was really happy for Michelle! Kevin Feige asked me if I would care & of course I didn’t, I really just wanted what was best for Michelle.|accessdate=05 February 2021|last=Gunn|first=James|date=05 February 2021|work=Twitter}}

